# Arrays
An array is a linear data structure that consists of elements of homogeneous type and stored in memory in the contiguous manner.

if ```arr``` is

| Memory Address | 1000 | 1004 | 1008 | 1012 |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Value  | 20  | 15 | 13| 17 |
|index| 0 | 1 | 2 | 3 |

 Java :-
arr[0] = 20
arr[1] = 15
arr[2] = 13
arr[3] = 17
